  "description": "First floor rear extension to create 2 x 1-bed flats",
  "decision_conditions": [
    "The proposed development would, due to its bulk, mass and scale in close proximity of existing flats on the site, result in harm to outlook and overshadowing, resulting in an increased sense of enclosure and loss of light to the detriment of the amenity of neighbouring properties, in direct contrast to the aims of London Plan Policy 3.5 and Policy DC61 of the LDF Core Strategy and Development Control Policies DPD.",
    "In the absence of a legal agreement to prevent future occupants from obtaining parking permits, the proposal will result in an overspill of carparking to the detriment of the surrounding area, contrary to the provisions of Policy DC33 of the Development Control Policies DPD.",
    "The proposed development would result in poor living conditions for future occupiers. The constraints of the site in conjunction with the design approach adopted would be to the detriment of the amenity of future occupiers. The units fail to meet the nationally described space standard and fail to provide adequate internal areas, privacy and built-in storage. The design will result in substandard living conditions for future occupants, in direct contrast to the aims of London Plan Policy 3.5 and Policy DC61 of the LDF Core Strategy and Development Control Policies DPD.",
    "The proposal, if granted planning permission on appeal, would be liable for Havering and Mayor of London Community Infrastructure Levy (CIL). Based upon the information supplied with the application, the CIL payable would be £9375 (Havering CIL) + £1875 (London Mayor CIL). Further details with regard to CIL are available from the Council's website."
